## Setup Instructions

### 1. Copy Environment Template
```bash
cp .env.example .env
cp .env.example .env.development
cp .env.example .env.staging
cp .env.example .env.production
```

### 2. Configure Secrets
```bash
# Using environment variables
export MONGODB_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -base64 32)
export REDIS_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -base64 32)
export JWT_SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 48)
```

### 3. Validate Configuration
```bash
# Check if all required variables are set
npm run validate:env

# Check for missing secrets
npm run check:secrets
```

### 4. Load into Application
```bash
# Development
source .env.development

# Production (using a secrets manager)
kubectl create secret generic going-platform-secrets --from-env-file=.env.production
```

---

## Security Best Practices

✅ Never commit .env files to version control
✅ Use different secrets for each environment
✅ Rotate secrets regularly (every 90 days)
✅ Use a secrets manager (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
✅ Enable audit logging for secret access
✅ Restrict environment variable access by role
✅ Use strong passwords (min 32 characters)
✅ Enable MFA for sensitive services (PagerDuty, Slack, etc.)

---

## Monitoring & Troubleshooting

### Check Configuration
```bash
# Verify all services are configured correctly
npm run verify:config

# Check service connectivity
npm run health:check

# View current configuration (sanitized)
npm run config:show
```

### Common Issues

Issue: Rate limiting service not responding
- Check Redis connection: redis-cli ping
- Check service logs: docker logs going-platform-redis

Issue: Alerts not reaching Slack
- Verify bot token: curl -X POST https://slack.com/api/auth.test
- Check integration logs: docker logs going-platform-slack-integration

Issue: Database queries slow
- Check MongoDB: mongodb://user:pass@host:27017/db?serverSelectionTimeoutMS=5000
- Enable profiling: db.setProfilingLevel(1, { slowms: 200 })

